product_name: BuxomPlump Shot Plumping and Smoothing Lip Serum Gloss with Peptides and Hyaluronic Acid
summary: SummaryBuxom's Plump Shot Lip Serum is a clinically shown plumping lip serum stacked with hyaluronic acid and moisturizing botanical oils for your plumpest pout ever.
details: DetailsBenefitsClinical plumping results - no pain necessaryBuxom's most advanced plumper, visibly plumps lips by 24%Leaves your lips with an invigorating sensationNatural, soft shine finishFormulated without parabens, mineral oil or petroleumKey IngredientsAdvances peptides & tri-peptides help to promote fuller-looking lips over timeHyaluronic acid filling spheres help hydrate, smooth & fill the appearance of fine lines and wrinklesTsubaki, avocado & jojoba oils help to condition & smooth the appearance of fine lines and wrinklesInvigorating complex creates a fresh, cooling sensation & stimulates blood flow to the surface of the lips for a gently flushed effectResearch ResultsClinically shown to visibly plump lips by 24% & reduce lines and wrinkles by 34%*94% of users saw instant results**93% of users said their lips appear plumper**100% of users said their lips appear smoother**100% of users said this product left a comfortable, tingling sensation on lips***In a U.S. clinical study of 30 people.**In a US consumer study with 30 women.Item 2578458How To UseWear by itself as a nourishing lip treatment or layer over lip color for a volumizing shot of shine.Apply Plump Shot Lip Serum to lip surface only, staying within your lip lines. For a plump and pampered, glossy pout, layer over Power-Full Plump Lip Balm. For a lush, next level glam look, layer over lip color or mix with Full-On Plumping Lip Polish or Full-On Plumping Lip Cream to add clinical plumping power and a volumizing shot of shine.Power-Full Plump Lip Balm, Full-On Plumping Lip Polish & Full-On Plumping Lip Cream sold separately.IngredientsFiller: Hydrogenated Poly (C6-14 Olefin), Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Oil, Ethylene/Propylene/Styrene Copolymer, Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Collagen, Camellia Japonica Seed Oil, Benzyl Nicotinate, Menthone Glycerin Acetal, Sodium Hyaluronate, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Portulaca Pilosa Extract, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-38, Mentha Piperita (Peppermint) Oil, Butylene/Ethylene/Styrene Copolymer, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Silica Dimethyl Silylate, Butylene Glycol, Caprylyl Glycol, Hexylene Glycol, Tribehenin, Sorbitan Isostearate, Lactic Acid, Tocopheryl Acetate, Cetearyl Ethylhexanoate, Sucrose Cocoate, Water (Aqua/Eau), Alcohol, Vanillin, Limonene, Phenoxyethanol.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Wear by itself as a nourishing lip treatment or layer over lip color for a volumizing shot of shine.Apply Plump Shot Lip Serum to lip surface only, staying within your lip lines. For a plump and pampered, glossy pout, layer over Power-Full Plump Lip Balm. For a lush, next level glam look, layer over lip color or mix with Full-On Plumping Lip Polish or Full-On Plumping Lip Cream to add clinical plumping power and a volumizing shot of shine.Power-Full Plump Lip Balm, Full-On Plumping Lip Polish & Full-On Plumping Lip Cream sold separately.

reviews.headline: Plumping with no pain!!
reviews.comments: this was my first time trying a plumping lip gloss and I immediately fell in love with this product!! not sticky or drying either!

reviews.headline: Beautiful shine, doesn't last
reviews.comments:
Beautiful color (3 coats).
Color/plumbing effect wears off quickly. 
I'm bummed.

reviews.headline: Not glossy but plump works 100%
reviews.comments: I like the finish on the lip polish better than the plump shot.. its not as shiny or glossy, it more so just coats your skin & plumps it up. I might even try adding the lip polish over plump shot. Has a good color/sparkles depending on which one you choose but doesnt give a glossy finish and I usually like that for my lip glosses.

reviews.headline: Disappointed
reviews.comments: It's clear.  No plumping action detected. Can't say it's very good at anything.

reviews.headline: Amazing - nothing like it
reviews.comments:
It's lightweight like a lip oil, hydrating, gives a plump without major irritation. Has a slight burn tingle but also has a minty cooling effect. WOW It's amazing- nothing compares. 

Yes, it will create a redness & plump where you apply it! So don't apply it outside of your lips like some negative reviews lol Silly goose.

reviews.headline: Similar result to TooFaced but no burn
reviews.comments:
Plumps really well, has a mild cooling sensation. Just thick enough to last a while without being sticky at all. Super hydrating. Love that it comes in clear. Smells/tastes amazing, like thin mint cookies. Tied for first place with TooFaced lip injection ðŸ¥‡

To all the people that put "caused redness" as a con, what do you think "plumping" means? It draws blood to the area, that'sâ€¦the point

reviews.headline: aaaaaamazing results. slight burn but totally doable.
reviews.comments: I absolutely love it. I'm amazed at the results I got. of course I didn't take pictures, I always forget! well worth the $29 spent. makes your lips feel incredibly soft and smooth as well as well as plump

reviews.headline: Be careful
reviews.comments: Had a horrible reaction the entire left side of my face and lip swoll. It wont allow me to add a picture for whatever reason. If you are prone to hives or contact dermatitis stay far away from this. Besdies that I liked the resultsâ€¦ it just went south fast. If you dont have this issue youll probably benefit grately from buying it.

reviews.headline: Not worth the money
reviews.comments: I tried all day to get some plumping, didn't feel any burn. Maybe they forgot the good stuff.

reviews.headline: Yes! I will buy every time
reviews.comments: I love how it gives a little plump but not to much and doesn't sting

reviews.headline: Not as described
reviews.comments: This is a warm tingle, I I I bought this based on the description. It says cooling but it kind of burns.

reviews.headline: Ordered weeks ago still haven't received it
reviews.comments: Ordered online weeks ago, still not received

reviews.headline: Burned my lips
reviews.comments: After about 5 min of havung this on, my lips started burning so badly i had to wash it off.

reviews.headline: A picker's solution
reviews.comments: My lips peel, making me look like I have a communicable disease (because I can't not pick at them when they peel). I probably shouldn't put product on open skin, but I did to try to even out the tone. Not only did it not hurt at all, it DID even the tone (I got hypnotic garnet). It also blurs those bothersome lines on my lips. I love lip plumpers and this is the only one I've tried that doesn't give me a reaction and make my lips burn and itch, which only exacerbates my picking issue. (Although, a friend asked me what I was wearing - so I told her, then when she tried it, it gave her a reaction so be careful.) My only complaints are the cost and it doesn't taste great; I ingested a little via drinking and anxious lip smoothing and it kinda numbed my throat. Just try not to eat it. Or pay full price for it.

reviews.headline: False advertising!
reviews.comments: This so-called plumping lip gloss absolutely does no plumping. The only thing I can say is that at least you get an okay lip gloss to wear in your non-plumped lips.

reviews.headline: burning
reviews.comments: Returning as its burning.

reviews.headline: Not what I expected
reviews.comments: Not happy with it

reviews.headline: Feels like a slap in the face - literally
reviews.comments: The burning and stinging were way beyond the usual plumping tingle - it felt like I rubbed hot pepper on my lips, or like someone slapped me right across the mouth. Super unpleasant. On top of that, it left my lips dry, tight, and uncomfortable for hours. There was no noticeable plump, just pain. I won't be using this again and definitely don't recommend it.

reviews.headline: I love this Lip Serum
reviews.comments: Buxom always makes the best products. I love this serum.

reviews.headline: Love Love Love
reviews.comments: Love the Buxom plump shot. Gives the look and feel of plump juicy lips. Tingles a little bit just enough to let you know, hey I'm doing my job. The color dolly babe is a favorite of mine. Goes on smooth and stays on well. Def worth the try!

faceoff_negative.comments:
First things first, I was given this product for free in exchange for a review.

Overall, I do enjoy this lip serum/gloss and will continue to use it, would be happy to receive it as a gift, however I don't think this is something I would purchase unless it was on sale for a REALLY good deal.  

Compared to other lip plumping products I've used around the same price point, any plumping effect is very minimal.  I don't think the product boasts *huge* plumping effects (18% plumper according to Buxom) but it's hard to tell if the product is actually plumping your lips or if the product is giving the illusion of plumper lips due to how glossy it is.  I really love how it looks either way, but compared to other products I'm not super impressed on that front.

I will say that this product is VERY comfortable to wear and has been flattering to wear on it's own and over other lip products.  It plays well layered on top of other lipsticks I've worn and wears very well over time.  My lips definitely feel hydrated and comfortable for hours after application (and even after eating, which is nice!)  The tingle is also very mild, no burning at all with this one.  It feels really nice and refreshing actually.

Bottom line, I enjoy using this lip serum.  It's nice but expensive for what it is, which is mostly a hydrating lip gloss and debatable if it's actually plumping or giving the illusion of a plump lip.  I would have a hard time recommending it over something else.  But if you really love the Buxom brand and are curious to try it out, I'd say buy it on sale.
faceoff_negative.headline: Great lipgloss, very minor plumping
